From: Andrew Morton <akpm@linux-foundation.org>
Date: Fri, 27 Mar 2026 17:21:05 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] liveupdate-initialize-incoming-flb-state-before-finish-fix

remove unneeded braces, per Pasha

Cc: Leo Timmins <leotimmins1974@gmail.com>
Cc: Mike Rapoport <rppt@kernel.org>
Cc: Pasha Tatashin <pasha.tatashin@soleen.com>
Cc: Pratyush Yadav <pratyush@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Andrew Morton <akpm@linux-foundation.org>
---
 kernel/liveupdate/luo_flb.c | 3 +--
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/kernel/liveupdate/luo_flb.c b/kernel/liveupdate/luo_flb.c
index 855af655b09b..6c89a9a25281 100644
--- a/kernel/liveupdate/luo_flb.c
+++ b/kernel/liveupdate/luo_flb.c
@@ -210,9 +210,8 @@ static void luo_flb_file_finish_one(struct liveupdate_flb *flb)
 		}
 	}
 
-	scoped_guard(mutex, &private->incoming.lock) {
+	scoped_guard(mutex, &private->incoming.lock)
 		count = --private->incoming.count;
-	}
 
 	if (!count) {
 		struct liveupdate_flb_op_args args = {0};
-- 
2.47.3

